  "instructions":"Read all instructions carefully before you begin writing. Write your full name and index number on the answer booklet as they appear on your registration form. DO NOT write your names or index number on any additional answer sheets. Do not open this paper until you are instructed to do so. Use only a BLUE or BLACK pen for writing answers, and a PENCIL for drawings. Calculators and mathematical instruments may be used where necessary. Show all working steps for calculation questions to earn full marks. Diagrams should be clearly drawn with all labels. Crossing out and rewriting is allowed. Only the final answer will be marked.",
   "answerKey":{
      "1":"a) Magnetic pole b) Magnetic field c) Demagnetized",
      "2":"a) iii – the medium through which the message is transmitted b) ii – Fiber optic cable c) ii – resistor, capacitor, transistor d) iv – ordinary diode",
      "3":"a) iii – Fulcrum b) ii – load/effort c) ii – effort; load d) i – wheel and axle",
      "4":"a) TRUE b) TRUE c) FALSE d) FALSE",
      "5":"a) TRUE b) FALSE (potential energy converts to kinetic energy) c) FALSE (geothermal = heat from Earth's interior)",
      "6":"a) iv – A = Negative, B = Positive (field lines go from positive to negative; arrows show B is positive, A is negative) b) iii – electric field intensity c) i – Q/(4πε₀ d) d) iii – paint spraying",
      "7":"a) Speed → iv [LT⁻ ¹] b) Density → iii [ML⁻ ³] c) Acceleration → iv [LT⁻ ²] d) Energy → i [ML²T⁻ ²]",
      "8":"a) Renewable energy sources can be naturally replenished in a short time and are available indefinitely (e.g., solar, wind). Non-renewable energy sources took millions of years to form and cannot be replaced once used (e.g., fossil fuels). b) i) Any one of: solar energy, wind power, hydroelectric power, geothermal energy, biomass ii) Any one of: coal, petroleum/oil, natural gas, uranium/nuclear fuel, minerals",
      "9":"a) Statement C: At t=1s, a runner is moving at 4 m/s west b) It specifies both the speed (4 m/s), the direction (west), and the exact instant in time (t = 1 s). Instantaneous velocity requires speed, direction, and a specific point in time.",
      "10":"a) Real transformers have losses due to: (i) resistance (copper) losses in the coil windings, and (ii) eddy current and hysteresis losses in the iron core / magnetic flux leakage. b) Thicker wires have lower electrical resistance (R = ρL/A; larger A = lower R). Lower resistance means less power lost as heat (P = I²R), making transmission more efficient. c) Step-down transformer (the distribution transformer reduces high transmission voltage to household level). d) Electricity at home is used for lighting, heating/cooling, powering appliances (TV, radio, computer, refrigerator, etc.).",
      "11":"a) i) The pushing force is equal to or less than the friction force, so the net horizontal force is zero – the brick remains stationary. ii) The weight (downward force) is exactly balanced by the normal reaction force from the table surface (Newton's 3rd Law). b) i) Linear momentum P = mv increases, because the constant resultant force causes constant acceleration (Newton's 2nd Law: F=ma), increasing velocity over time. ii) The sliding brick generates heat (friction converts kinetic energy to thermal energy) and/or produces sound.",
      "12":"a) iii) 0.5 m/s² [Using v² = u² + 2as: 15² - 10² = 2a(125), 125 = 250a, a = 0.5 m/s²] b) iv) 10 s [Using v = u + at: 15 = 10 + 0.5t, t = 5/0.5 = 10 s]",
      "13":"a) P = E/t = 2.88×10⁴ / 600 = 48 W = 0.048 kW; Energy in kWh = 0.048 kW × (1/6) h = 0.008 kWh b) P = U × I; U = P/I = 48/4 = 12 V",
      "14":"a) Impedance decreases. For a capacitor, Z = Xₙ = 1/(2πfC). As f increases, Z decreases (inversely proportional). b) rms current increases. Iᵣₘₛ = Vᵣₘₛ / Z = Vᵣₘₛ × 2πfC. As f increases, Iᵣₘₛ increases (directly proportional).",
      "15":"Without the hydrosphere: There would be no liquid water on Earth's surface. Living cells could not carry out normal functions – all life would cease to exist. There would be no habitat for aquatic organisms (fish, crocodiles, etc.). No evaporation, so no clouds could form, meaning no rainfall and no precipitation. Desertification would cover the entire planet. The climate regulation provided by oceans would be lost, leading to extreme temperature variations.",
      "16":"c) i) Power of converging lens: P₁ = 1/f = 1/0.25 m = +4 D ii) Power of diverging lens: P₂ = 1/f = 1/(-0.10 m) = -10 D iii) Total power: P = P₁ + P₂ = 4 + (-10) = -6 D iv) The combination is DIVERGING because the total power is negative (-6 D).",
      "17":"b) Procedure: Connect the circuit as drawn. Close the switch. Set the rheostat to different positions to vary the current. For each setting, record the ammeter reading (I) and the voltmeter reading (V). Repeat for at least 5 different current values. c) Analysis: Plot a graph of V (y-axis) vs. I (x-axis). Calculate the slope of the best-fit line. The slope = V/I = R (resistance). If the graph is a straight line through the origin, Ohm's Law (V = IR) is verified. d) Safety precautions: (i) Do not leave the circuit connected for long periods to prevent overheating. (ii) Ensure all connections are tight to avoid sparks. (iii) Do not exceed the rated current of the components.",
      "18":"b) i) 2500.0 ml ÷ 1000 = 2.5 L ii) 30 + 273 = 303 K iii) Charles's Law: V₁ /T₁ = V₂ /T₂ → V₂ = V₁ × T₂ /T₁ = 2.5 × 283/303 = 2.335 L ≈ 2.34 L c) Combined Gas Law: P₁ V₁ /T₁ = P₂ V₂ /T₂ → T₂ = T₁ × (P₂ V₂ )/(P₁ V₁ ) = 310 × (3.5×12)/(2.0×15) = 310 × 42/30 = 434 K d) Gay-Lussac's Law: P₁ /T₁ = P₂ /T₂ → T₁ = T₂ × P₁ /P₂ = 312.5 × 1.40/2.38 = 183.8 K",
      "19":"a) i) Volume displaced = 10⁻ ³ m³ (same as balloon volume) ii) Weight = ρ × V × g = 1000 × 10⁻ ³ × 9.81 = 9.81 N (proved) iii) Buoyant force = 9.81 N. The balloon floats completely submerged because the buoyant force equals the weight of water displaced, which equals the weight of the balloon contents (water), so the net force is zero. b) i) Buoyant force = ρᵤᵃᵣᵉᵗᵉᴿ × V × g = 1000 × 10⁻ ³ × 9.81 = 9.81 N ii) Weight of wood = mg = 0.5 × 9.81 = 4.905 N iii) The wood will float PARTIALLY IMMERSED. Buoyant force (9.81 N) > Weight (4.905 N), so net upward force exists. Wood rises until buoyant force equals its weight. Since density of wood (0.5/0.001 = 500 kg/m³) < density of water (1000 kg/m³), it floats partially submerged.",
      "20":"a) i) Solids: Conduction ii) Liquids: Convection b) Heat is a form of energy transferred due to a temperature difference, measured in Joules. Temperature is a measure of the average kinetic energy of particles in a substance, measured in Kelvin or Celsius. c) i) Initial volume = length × width × height = 20 cm × 10 cm × 5 cm = 1000 cm³ = 1 × 10⁻ ³ m³ ii) Coefficient of volume expansion γ = 3α = 3 × 1.2 × 10⁻ ⁵ = 3.6 × 10⁻ ⁵ /°C iii) ΔV = γ × V₀ × ΔT = 3.6 × 10⁻ ⁵ × 1000 cm³ × (40−10) = 3.6 × 10⁻ ⁵ × 1000 × 30 = 1.08 cm³",
      "21":"a) i) Mass: Balance / beam balance / electronic balance ii) Distance: Metre rule / measuring tape b) Formula: a = F/m (Newton's Second Law). Since mass is constant in this experiment, acceleration is directly proportional to force. Alternatively, from kinematics: a = (v² – u²) / (2s) or a = (v – u) / t using motion equations. c) Graph: Plot Force (N) on y-axis vs Acceleration (m/s²) on x-axis. Points should be approximately linear: (0.40, 0.20), (0.52, 0.25), (0.60, 0.30), (0.68, 0.35), (0.80, 0.40), (1.00, 0.50). Draw a straight best-fit line through the plotted points. d) i) The graph shows that force is directly proportional to acceleration (linear relationship through origin). As the acceleration increases, the force applied also increases proportionally. ii) Slope = ΔF/Δa = (0.50 – 0.20)/(1.00 – 0.40) = 0.30/0.60 = 0.5 kg. The slope represents the mass of the cart (m = F/a = slope). Mass of cart = 0.5 kg. e) The graph passed through all points because the experiment was performed under ideal/controlled conditions, the measurements were very precise, or systematic/random errors were minimized."
